==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|byen|lang=enm}}, {{term|biggen|lang=enm}}, {{term|buggen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|bycgan|bycġan|to buy, pay for, acquire, redeem, ransom, procure, get done, sell|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|bugjanan|to buy|lang=en}}, of uncertain origin. Perhaps from {{proto|Indo-European|bhūgh-|to bend|lang=en}}, or from {{proto|Indo-European|bheugh-|to take away, deliver|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|by||to buy, purchase|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|buggian|lang=osx}}, {{term|buggean||to buy|lang=osx}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|byggja||to procure a wife, lend at interest, let out|lang=non}}, Gothic {{term|𐌱𐌿𐌲𐌾𐌰𐌽||tr=bugjan|lang=got|to buy|sc=Goth}}.

